definition.value: A carnitinium that is the conjugate acid of (S)-carnitine.
Cyclopropane and its derivatives formed by substitution.
A carbocyclic compound that is cyclopropene and its derivatives formed by substitution.
Carboxamides RC(=O)NR'R'' where R is a cyclopropyl group.
A carbotricyclic compound that is (+)-epi-isozizaene in which the hydrogens at position 5 have been replaced by an oxo group.

A benzothiazolium ion resulting from the methylation of the nitrogen of the benzothiazole group of N-[4-(1,3-benzothiazol-2-ylmethylene)-1-phenyl-1,4-dihydroquinolin-2-yl]-N',N'-dimethyl-N-propylpropane-1,3-diamine. A cationic unsymmetrical cyanine dye that binds to double-stranded DNA and is used as a nucleic acid stain in molecular biology.
An organolithium compound where an alkyl group is bound to a lithium atom.
An organolithium compound where an alkenyl group is bound to a lithium atom.
An organolithium compound where an alkynyl group is bound to a lithium atom.
An organolithium compound where an aryl group is bound to a lithium atom.
Vinyllithium and its substutution derivatives.

A cyanine dye that is 1-phenylquinoline which is substituted at position 2 by a bis[3-(dimethylamino)propyl]amino group and at position 4 by a (3-methyl-1,3-benzothiazol-3-ium-2-yl)methylene group. The counter ion is not stated. A fluorochrome that selectively binds double-stranded DNA and has characteristics similar to that of SYBR-Green I.

A racemate consisting of equal amounts of arformoterol (the active enantiomer) and (S,S)-formoterol (the inactive enantiomer). Its fumaric acid salt is used as a direct-acting sympathomimetic and bronchodilator for the treatment of chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (any progressive respiratory disease that makes it harder to breathe over time, such as chronic bronchitis and emphysema).
Halogenated cyanine compound that binds nucleic acids.
A hydroxynaphthalene that is naphthalene-1,4-diol and its C-substituted derivatives.
Any sugar having one or more alcoholic hydrogen moieties replaced by amino groups.
An alkynyllithium compound resulting from the replacement of one of the hydrogens of acetylene by lithium.
An organomagnesium halide where the organyl group is an alkyl group.
An organomagnesium halide where the organyl group is an aryl group.
A compound containing at least one carbon-rhodium bond.
A compound containing at least one carbon-zinc bond.
An organozinc compound where the zinc atom is bound to two alkyl groups.
mu-chloro-bridged dimer of iridium(III) bis [3-(benzothiazol-2-yl)-7-(diethylamino)coumarin)]
An organozinc compound where the zinc atom is bound to two aryl groups.
An organorhodium compound containing a carbon-rhodium double bond.
